{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19658", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19658/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19658/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/19658/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/19658", "id": 51417830, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWU1MTQxNzgzMA==", "number": 19658, "title": "`|| true` after macro invocation in StmtExpr parses oddly", "user": {"login": "tomjakubowski", "id": 667901, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzkwMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/667901?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski", "html_url": "https://github.com/tomjakubowski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 1, "created_at": "2014-12-09T11:42:14Z", "updated_at": "2014-12-09T13:38:11Z", "closed_at": "2014-12-09T13:38:11Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "For example:\n\n``` rust\n#![feature(macro_rules)]\n\nmacro_rules! foo { () => { true } }\n\nfn baz() -> bool {\n    foo!() || true\n}\n\nfn main() { }\n```\n\nWhen compiled, produces these errors:\n\n```\nfoo.rs:3:28: 3:32 error: mismatched types: expected `()`, found `bool` (expected (), found bool)\nfoo.rs:3 macro_rules! foo { () => { true } }\n                                    ^~~~\nfoo.rs:3:1: 3:36 note: in expansion of foo!\nfoo.rs:6:5: 6:14 note: expansion site\nfoo.rs:6:12: 6:19 error: mismatched types: expected `bool`, found `|| -> bool` (expected bool, found fn)\nfoo.rs:6     foo!() || true\n                    ^~~~~~~\nerror: aborting due to 2 previous errors\n```\n\nWhereas something like this does parse as intended:\n\n``` rust\n#![feature(macro_rules)]\n\nmacro_rules! foo { () => { true } }\n\nfn main() {\n    if foo!() || true {\n\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe error is remedied by surrounding the whole expression in parentheses, turning it into a `return` statement, or doing something like `let x = foo!() || true; x`.\n", "closed_by": {"login": "tomjakubowski", "id": 667901, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY2NzkwMQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/667901?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski", "html_url": "https://github.com/tomjakubowski", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/tomjakubowski/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.g